  </intervention>
  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Polisensitized patients with allergic rinitis and rhinoconjunctivitis with or without
        associated mild or moderate asthma
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients aged between 5 and 60 years who present rhinitis or allergic
             rhinoconjunctivitis caused by IgE-mediated sensitization to more than one allergen
             source with or without mild / moderate asthma.

          2. Patients eligible for immunotherapy treatment with Allergovac Poliplus according to
             investigator criteria.

          3. Patients must provide written informed consent. It is the case of children , the legal
             representative or tutor of the child must sign the inform consent form.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Patients that according to the investigator criteria may present difficulties for
             understanding the patient information sheet, completing the questionnaires and
             self-administered scales.

          2. Patients that according to the investigator may present difficulties to complete the
             patient diary.

          3. Patients who are participating in another clinical trial or observational study.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
    <minimum_age>5 Years</minimum_age>
    <maximum_age>60 Years</maximum_age>
    <healthy_volunteers>No</healthy_volunteers>
  </eligibility>
